George L. KELLER v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 1967. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Sept. 13, 1939. Forrest McCutcheon, of Oklahoma City, Okl., for appellant. Charles E. Dierker, U. S. Atty., of Shawnee, Okl., and Wade H. Loofbourrow, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Oklahoma City, Okl.

Before LEWIS, PHILLIPS and BRAT-TON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed at appeilant’s costs, for failure to prosecute, on motion of appellee.
